# Build Observation Recall: Typesense Projection + sessions-search Replacement

## Step

Joel's charter (2026-07-12): observation pages "should absolutely be groomed
into a Typesense collection and replace existing joelclaw session search cli."

Build: (1) an `observations` Typesense collection as a DETERMINISTIC,
REBUILDABLE projection of `dark-wizard/.brain/observations/*.svx` (files are
truth — see the storage decision record); fields from schema-v1 frontmatter +
gist + observations/decisions sections; sensitive pages indexed (local recall
is chartered) but flagged. (2) An idempotent indexer
(`joelclaw observations index --rebuild`). (3) `joelclaw sessions search`
defaults to the observation layer — results return the canonical
brain.joelclaw.com page URL + sessionId, sensitive results labeled; raw
chunk search demoted to `--raw`. (4) Fix the stale `dark-wizard` ssh-host
default in the sessions code (flagg-rename fallout, found 2026-07-12).

Distilled-first recall is the ADR functional bar made concrete: "every
context understands the work." The rhizomatic-briefing integration stays in
map fog — this ticket is collection + CLI.

## Resolution (2026-07-12)

Shipped: `observations` collection (75 docs, deterministic projection,
`joelclaw observations index --rebuild`); `joelclaw sessions search` defaults
to the distilled layer (gist + canonical brain.joelclaw.com URL + sensitive
labeling), `--raw` preserved; stale `dark-wizard` ssh default fixed. Steering
re-verified receipts independently. Unblocks build-voice-observation-recall.
